WEBVTT

00:02.264 --> 00:05.133
And here's another
interesting weather fact.

00:05.135 --> 00:07.802
Another? Great!

00:07.804 --> 00:11.172
Changes in jet streams
can affect the speed

00:11.174 --> 00:13.474
at which the Earth
rotates on its axis,

00:13.476 --> 00:16.844
so bad weather can actually
make the day longer.

00:16.846 --> 00:19.714
Well, there must be a hell
of a storm somewhere.

00:21.550 --> 00:23.618
Joke if you must,

00:23.620 --> 00:25.720
but you're going to
miss these moments.

00:25.722 --> 00:27.488
With Leonard home
in a few days,

00:27.490 --> 00:30.691
this was your last time driving
me to the grocery store.

00:30.693 --> 00:32.659
You know,
I will miss this.

00:32.662 --> 00:35.797
I'll tell you what,
if my apples are mealy,

00:35.799 --> 00:40.134
we'll hit the produce section
for one last crazy blowout.

00:40.136 --> 00:42.336
Heck, you can even
push the cart.

00:42.338 --> 00:46.674
Please don't take my looking
forward to Leonard's return

00:46.676 --> 00:50.011
as criticism of the job you've
been doing in his absence.

00:50.013 --> 00:51.479
I won't.

00:52.548 --> 00:56.184
That criticism will come later
in your report card.

00:56.186 --> 00:58.319
Yeah, I didn't stay
for the detention,

00:58.321 --> 01:00.388
I'm not gonna read
the report card.

01:03.792 --> 01:04.759
Hello.

01:04.760 --> 01:05.893
(screams)
Leonard!

01:05.895 --> 01:07.228
Shh, shh.
Hi!

01:07.230 --> 01:08.629
Keep your voice down.
Oh, my God.

01:08.631 --> 01:09.931
You weren't supposed
to be here till Sunday!

01:09.933 --> 01:11.165
We finished
the experiment early,

01:11.167 --> 01:12.867
so I thought I'd come home
and surprise you.

01:12.869 --> 01:14.368
Oh, my gosh, why
are we whispering?

01:14.370 --> 01:15.269
I didn't tell Sheldon,

01:15.271 --> 01:16.971
so we could have
a few days alone.

01:16.973 --> 01:18.906
Oh, that is
so romantic.

01:18.908 --> 01:21.142
Uh, sure,
that's why I did it.

01:22.111 --> 01:25.646
Oh... I just cannot
believe you're here.

01:25.648 --> 01:27.081
SHELDON: Penny, it's
your lucky day!

01:27.083 --> 01:29.117
Three of the eggs are
clearly not jumbo.

01:29.119 --> 01:30.485
Grab your keys.

01:32.354 --> 01:35.990
♪ Our whole universe
was in a hot, dense state ♪

01:35.992 --> 01:39.327
♪ Then nearly 14 billion years
ago expansion started... Wait! ♪

01:39.329 --> 01:40.962
♪ The Earth began to cool

01:40.964 --> 01:43.498
♪ The autotrophs began to drool,
Neanderthals developed tools ♪

01:43.500 --> 01:46.167
♪ We built the Wall
♪ <i>We built the pyramids</i> ♪

01:46.169 --> 01:48.836
♪ Math, Science, History,
unraveling the mystery ♪

01:48.838 --> 01:50.738
♪ That all started
with a big bang ♪

01:50.740 --> 01:51.740
♪ <i>Bang!</i> ♪

01:51.741 --> 01:55.740
<font color=#00FF00>♪ The Big Bang Theory 7x02 ♪</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>The Deception Verification</font>
